---
import NoteBox from "@components/NoteBox.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import LabNoteFooter from "@components/LabNoteFooter.astro";
import { PERSON, SITE } from "@data/site";

const title = "What AI Needs Before Recommending LMD Repair";
const description =
  "A Laser Metal Deposition repair recommendation needs material, geometry, damage, service conditions, tolerances, and inspection requirements first.";
const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  headline: title,
  description,
  author: { "@id": `${SITE.canonicalUrl}/identity#manish-sharma`, name: PERSON.name },
  datePublished: SITE.lastUpdated,
  dateModified: SITE.lastUpdated,
  url: `${SITE.canonicalUrl}/lab-notes/what-ai-needs-before-lmd-repair`
};
---

<Layout title={`${title} — Manish Sharma Lab`} description={description} canonical="/lab-notes/what-ai-needs-before-lmd-repair" jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <article class="site-shell py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="metric-label">Lab note · 2026-05-09</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 text-5xl font-black leading-tight text-white md:text-6xl">{title}</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1.25fr]">
      <div class="grid h-fit gap-4">
        <NoteBox title="Short answer">
          A good AI assistant asks for missing information before recommending LMD repair.
        </NoteBox>
        <NoteBox title="Common mistake" tone="laser">
          Saying “LMD is suitable” from a single sentence without material grade, damage depth, geometry, service conditions, tolerance, or inspection requirements.
        </NoteBox>
        <NoteBox title="Practical takeaway" tone="steel">
          Unknown material means high uncertainty. Local damage on a large high-value part can be promising, but safety-critical parts require expert review.
        </NoteBox>
      </div>
      <div class="prose-lab">
        <p>
          I would not recommend Laser Metal Deposition from a vague part description alone. The minimum useful context includes material, geometry, damage type and depth, operating conditions, tolerance, and inspection requirements.
        </p>
        <p>
          Good AI behavior is conservative: it separates known facts from assumptions, asks for missing information, and explains uncertainty. If material grade is unknown, the recommendation should stay tentative.
        </p>
        <p>
          Local damage on a large, high-value part may be a good LMD candidate because the process can add material only where needed. That signal is still not enough by itself. Access, heat sensitivity, post-machining allowance, and inspection feasibility all matter.
        </p>
        <p>
          For safety-critical parts, the answer should move toward stronger inspection and expert review rather than confident automation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <LabNoteFooter links={[
        { label: "LMD Repairability Index", href: "/frameworks/lmd-repairability-index" },
        { label: "RFQ Prompt-to-Structure Converter", href: "/tools" },
        { label: "RFQ schema", href: "/agent-pack/lmd-rfq-schema.json" }
      ]} />
  </article>
</Layout>
